sp.p:
Bless'ee, Missey Zoe, here it be. Dere's a dish of
penpans — jess taste, Mas'r George — and here's fried bananas;
smell 'em, do, sa glosh.

I cannot find the entry in my husband's accounts;
but you, Mr. McClosky, can doubtless detect it. Zoe, bring
here the Judge's old desk, it is in the library.

No, I'm the skurriest crittur at a fight you ever see;
my legs have been too well brought up to stand and see my
body abused; I take good care of myself, I can tell you.

Come, Mrs. Peyton, take my arm;
hush! here's the other one; she's a little too thoroughbred —
too much of the greyhound, but the heart's there, I believe.

Oh! law, sar. Dat debbel, 'Closky — he tore hisself
from de gentleman — knock me down — take away my light,
and throwed it on de turpentine barrels — de ship's on fire!
